Responsibilities:

  Involved in the entire website programming development, including existing website programming development.
  Ability to schedule and deliver based on the company requirements, take ownership and be responsible for the technical aspects and project deadlines
  Able to develop website using PHP
  Ensure that website is compatible across all browsers.
  Ability to work on project without detailed instructions; taking the initiative with this job is important
  Provide onsite user training and technical support to customers


Requirements:

  Candidate must possess at least a Diploma / Degree in Computer Science or related area
  Strong knowledge in PHP, MySQL, HTML, HTML5, DHTML, CSS, AJAX, jQuery and Javascript
  Familiar with open source such as WordPress &amp; Magento
  Strong sense of programming logic, web usability and flow experience.
  Good knowledge in cross-browser applications.
  At least 1 year(s) of working experience in the related field
  At least 1-2 years of working experience in LAMP (Linux, Apache, MySQL, PHP)
  Able to use Photoshop, Illustrator, and/or other graphic editing skills will be an advantage
  Familiar with Mobile Application Development (iPhone / Anorid Apps) will be an advantage.

Location: Woodland
Working hours : 10 am to 7 pm